            <fr:title text="the positive part of a semidirected subset is semidirected">the positive part of a semidirected subset is semidirected</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Lemma</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[I\subseteq  A]]></fr:tex> be a semidirected subset of a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-001S.xml" title="pointed dcpo" addr="jms-001S" type="local">pointed</fr:link> dcpo <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex>; then the intersection <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[I \cap  A^+]]></fr:tex> is semidirected, where <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A^+]]></fr:tex> is the <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-001P.xml" title="the subdcpo spanned by positive elements" addr="jms-001P" type="local">subdcpo spanned by positive elements</fr:link>.</html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>2</fr:month><fr:day>16</fr:day></fr:date><fr:addr>jms-0028/0</fr:addr><fr:route>https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-0028/0.xml</fr:route><fr:title text="the positive part of a semidirected subset is semidirected › forest://jonmsterling/jms-0028/0"><fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-0028.xml" title="the positive part of a semidirected subset is semidirected" addr="jms-0028" type="local">the positive part of a semidirected subset is semidirected</fr:link> › jms-0028/0</fr:title><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
  <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[i,j]]></fr:tex> be two <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-001M.xml" title="the positive elements of a pointed dcpo" addr="jms-001M" type="local">positive</fr:link> elements of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[I]]></fr:tex>; we must show that there exists a positive element <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[k\in  I]]></fr:tex> such that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[i\sqsubseteq  k]]></fr:tex> and <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[j\sqsubseteq  k]]></fr:tex>. This follows immediately from the directedness of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[I]]></fr:tex> and <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-0029.xml" title="positivity is upward-closed" addr="jms-0029" type="local">the fact that positivity is monotone</fr:link>.</html:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
